<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,944,1187]" box="[151,558,944,971]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,944,971]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,944,1187]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,980,1007]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe. 
<collectingCountry box="[461,560,981,1007]" name="Portugal" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: two coastal provinces, one in the north (Minho) and one in the south (Estremadura) of the country.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,944,1187]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1053,1079]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Ecology.</emphasis>
Recorded exclusively from marshlands in 
<collectingCountry box="[774,873,1053,1079]" name="Portugal" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Portugal</collectingCountry>
. In northwestern Europe, it shows a distinct preference for salt marshes and brackish marshes (
<bibRefCitation author="Pollet, M." box="[649,785,1089,1115]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref34362" refString="Pollet, M. (2000) A documented Red List of the dolichopodid flies (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) of Flanders [in Dutch with English summary]. Communications of the Institute of Nature Conservation, 8, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2000">Pollet 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,944,1187]" box="[199,581,1124,1151]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1124,1151]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
2.3 (rare). Rare (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,944,1187]" box="[199,537,1160,1187]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,1160,1187]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Activity period.</emphasis>
